columns.name: BBL
columns.description: Borough, Block, and Lot is the parcel number system used to identify each unit of NYC real estate. It consists of three numbers: the borough, which is 1 digit the block number, which is up to 5 digits and the lot number, which is up to 4 digits.

columns.name: BIN
columns.description: NYC Building Identification Number as assigned by the Department of City Planning.

columns.name: BORO
columns.description: Boro codes are 1=Manhattan, 2=Bronx, 3=Brooklyn, 4=Queens, 5=Staten Island. Districts are written as 2 digit numbers range is 01 to 18. Blank if Vendor isn't located in New York City.

columns.description: Boro codes are 1=Manhattan, 2=Bronx, 3=Brooklyn, 4=Queens, 5=Staten Island. Districts are written as 2 digit numbers range is 01 to 18. Blank if Vendor isn't located in New York City.
